    "# Beginner Notebook: Pandas, Matplotlib, and numpy\n",
    "\n",
    "You can wrangle data using lists and dictionaries, but it's not as intuitive as working with, say, a spreadsheet. Fortunately, there are lots of libraries for Python that make it an even better tool for tabular data — way better than spreadsheet applications like Microsoft Excel or Google Sheets! One of the best known data science libraries is **pandas**, which allows you to organize data into **DataFrames**.\n",
    "\n",
    "- Read more: https://pandas.pydata.org/docs/getting_started/intro_tutorials/01_table_oriented.html"
   ]
  },
  {
