   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**NB**: The axis parameter defines the direction of the \"glue.\" It is the most important concept to master in pandas. \n",
    "- **axis=0** (Default): (Vertical), Stacks the second object under the first (adds rows).\n",
    "- **axis=1**: (Horizontal), Stacks the second object to the right of the first (adds columns)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- **DataFrame**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "2. **Pandas DataFrame**: A DataFrame is a two-dimensional labeled data structure with rows and columns. It's far more common.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Dimensions**: 2D.\n",
    "- **Analogy**: Similar to an entire Excel sheet or a SQL table.\n",
    "- **Key Feature**: It can be thought of as a dictionary-like container for Series objects, where each column is its own Series."
