   "source": [
    "## Importing Data\n",
    "## CSV Files\n",
    "CSV stands for Comma Separated Values, and it's a file type that allows data to be saved in a table. Data presented in a table is called structured data, because it adheres to the idea that there is a meaningful relationship between the columns and rows. The datasets we're using in this part of the course are all structured tables, but you'll see other arrangements of data as you move through your projects."
   ]
