    "# `.apply` function is used to apply functional operations using lambda\n",
    "car_sales_reset_shuffled[\"individual_price (per quantity)\"] = car_sales_reset_shuffled[\"price_usd\"].apply(lambda x: x / 2)\n",
    "car_sales_reset_shuffled.head()  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The way lambda function works here is that, for each data cell in axis=1 i.e(`price_usd` column) it takes the value as `x` then divide x by 2 and then store it into `x` for the corresponding value pair in each row."
   ]
